      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "From your answer I assume you are using the IBM JVM. (-Xdump is an IBM specific option.) If it is a recent version you can use -Xdump:directory=/dumps to relocate all the dump files with non-absolute paths set with one option instead of resetting all the different types of dumps. See: <a href=\"http://www.ibm.com/support/knowledgecenter/SSYKE2_7.0.0/com.ibm.java.lnx.70.doc/diag/tools/dumpagents_syntax.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">ibm.com/support/knowledgecenter/SSYKE2_7.0.0/&hellip;</a>"
    }, {
