    "last_activity_date" : 1478672878,
    "creation_date" : 1478672878,
    "answer_id" : 40501155,
    "question_id" : 40468498,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<pre><code>JAVA_OPTS=\"$JAVA_OPTS -Xdump:heap:label=/dumps/heapdump.%Y%m%d.%H%M%S.%pid.%seq.phd\" \nJAVA_OPTS=\"$JAVA_OPTS -Xdump:java:label=/dumps/javacore.%Y%m%d.%H%M%S.%pid.%seq.txt\" \nJAVA_OPTS=\"$JAVA_OPTS -Xdump:system:label=/dumps/core.%Y%m%d.%H%M%S.%pid.%seq.dmp\" \nJAVA_OPTS=\"$JAVA_OPTS -Xdump:snap:label=/dumps/Snap.%Y%m%d.%H%M%S.%pid.%seq.trc\" \n(Optional) JAVA_OPTS=\"$JAVA_OPTS -Xdump:what\" \n</code></pre>\n\n<p>You can change the JAVA_OPTS env variable or simple add individual -Xdump cmds from where you are running the code.\nlike <code>\njava -d64 -Xdump:heap:label=/${INFA_ROOT}/temp/heapdump.%Y%m%d.%H%M%S.%pid.%seq.phd -Xmx4g ...rest of the arrgs.</code></p>\n"
  } ],
