  "title" : "Java Heap dump location , unix command line",
  "body" : "<p>I am facing a issue in which my heapdump is more than 2gb or maybe even 3gb is some cases , Now the problem is the heap dump gets created in a location (/home) which is of around 1gb only so after 1gb of heapdump the server gets deadlock(No other process can run) \nI just want to change the location of the Heapdump.</p>\n\n<p>I am running my code on unix server , and increasing the size of /home dir is not an option.\nI have tried using -XX:HeapDumpPath but it is not working. \nPlease help me out here.</p>\n"
}